 same name as one of their installed languages.\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\nAllison\n\u003c/p\u003e","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"0782f66a529ccd24e18226f5eebab20a90bea166"},"timestamp":1257427689,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM1MDM0MTU=","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/508#issuecomment-3503415"},"message":"\u003cp\u003e\nFollowup from pmichaud:\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\nOn Sat, Aug 30, 2008 at 07:45:08AM -0700, Allison Randal via RT wrote:\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cblockquote class=\"citation\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\n As mentioned in RT \u003ca class=\"missing ticket\"\u003e#49168\u003c/a\u003e, I'm in favor of a --language flag,\n that selects the default PBC/PIR file to run, and passes all other\n arguments to the ':main' sub in that file. It can also select default\n paths based on the options set the the configuration file for that language.\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\nAgreed on the --language concept, although I think I prefer \"--prog\"\n(mentioned in \u003ca class=\"missing ticket\"\u003e#49168\u003c/a\u003e) to \"--language\". Not everything we might want\nto invoke in this manner is actually a compiler or language.\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\nIf we're agreed on this approach, I'll open a [todo] ticket for it.\nI might even write the patch to make it work. :-)\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\nPm\n\u003c/p\u003e","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"0782f66a529ccd24e18226f5eebab20a90bea166"},"timestamp":1257427720,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM1MDM0MTY=","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/508#issuecomment-3503416"},"message":"\u003cp\u003e\nFinally, a discussion occurred regarding whether or not fakeceutables would satisfy the spirit of the request. Answer? No.\n\u003c/p\u003e","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"d9b4aee65ce8c18d4a43eced1eecb0d154e1eebb"},"timestamp":1298633222,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29